Senior Advisor to the President Ivanka Trump participated in an event promoting access to coding and computer science education in K-12 schools. She discussed the administration's focus on aligning education with in-demand jobs in the modern economy. The Internet Association announced a $300 million investment from companies like Amazon, Facebook, Google, and Microsoft to improve computer science education programs. President Trump also signed a memorandum directing the Department of Education to invest $200 million annually in STEM and computer science education. Ivanka Trump aims to address the lack of resources in K-12 schools and provide them with the means to implement high-quality STEM and computer science programs.